messages.reasoning_content:
I see! The `OneUse_match::match` function at line 62-64 checks `V->hasOneUse()` FIRST, before calling `SubPattern.match(V)`.

This is important because if the zext has more than one use, the pattern won't match even if the subpattern would match.

But in our test case, the zext only has one use (the final add). So this should work.

